The low pass filter command, lpf, is part of a group of filter commands
consisting of bpf, hpf, and lpf.  These commands invoke the sox helper
program to apply a band pass, a high pass, or a low pass filter,
respectively, to the audio.  The usual default cutoff frequency is 3000
Hz, optimized for pitched samples (i.e., voice and music).  Only an
entire audio can be filtered.
